{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":4068,"name":"","username":"practicing01","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/p/b5e925/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-01-11T09:22:34.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello, I’ve got two scenes with a camera in each (1 ortho 1 perspective).  I’d like to have the scene with the ortho camera on top of the scene with the perspective camera (like if they were 2d layers).  Is this possible?  If so how would I go about doing this?  Thanks for your time.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:35.611Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":636,"reads":138,"readers_count":137,"score":3209.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/creating-minimap/2249/2","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Creating minimap","clicks":29},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/drawing-a-2d-rectangle-on-top-of-the-screen/1162/2","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Drawing a 2D rectangle on top of the screen","clicks":21},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/static-background-in-3d-scene/922/2","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Static Background in 3D Scene","clicks":12},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/fps-control-example/2059/3","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"FPS control example?","clicks":10},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/anaglyph-renderer/959/3","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Anaglyph Renderer","clicks":3},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/solved-change-models-on-second-viewport/2360/3","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"[Solved] Change models on second viewport","clicks":1},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/how-to-render-a-viewport-with-alpha-or-transparent-backgroun/798/2","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"How to render a viewport with alpha or transparent backgroun","clicks":1},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/improving-near-and-far-clipping/3049/3","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Improving near and far clipping","clicks":0},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/rendering-one-scene-on-to-another/2119/4","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Rendering one scene on to another","clicks":0},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/tech-task-game-dev-need-help/3160/2","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Tech Task - Game Dev. Need Help","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":140,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":4070,"name":"Lasse Öörni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2015-01-11T11:51:20.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThis question is similar to \u003ca href=\"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/render-3d-model-in-orthographic-mode/737/1\"\u003etopic753.html\u003c/a\u003e. Make 2 viewports (check the MultipleViewports sample) that have the same screen region, point each to the respective scene and camera, then use a different renderpath for the “on-top” scene, where you omit the “clear” command. If you get trouble with Z-buffering, then you can make the second renderpath clear depth but not color.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:35.742Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":137,"readers_count":136,"score":47.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"Lasse Öörni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/render-3d-model-in-orthographic-mode/737","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Render 3D Model in Orthographic mode","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":4071,"name":"","username":"practicing01","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/p/b5e925/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-01-11T15:11:07.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI’ve made two viewports/cams/scenes but I’m not seeing both scenes, just whichever is viewport 0.  Did I do something wrong with the renderpath stuff?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003eSpaceSimulationMenuSelect::SpaceSimulationMenuSelect(Context* context, Urho3DPlayer* main) :\n    Object(context)\n{\n\tmain_ = main;\n\telapsedTime_ = 0.0f;\n\n\tmain_-\u0026gt;cameraNode_-\u0026gt;RemoveAllChildren();\n\tmain_-\u0026gt;cameraNode_-\u0026gt;RemoveAllComponents();\n\tmain_-\u0026gt;cameraNode_-\u0026gt;Remove();\n\n\tscene_ = new Scene(main_-\u0026gt;GetContext());\n\tcameraNode_ = new Node(main_-\u0026gt;GetContext());\n\n\tRenderer* renderer = GetSubsystem\u0026lt;Renderer\u0026gt;();\n\tResourceCache* cache = GetSubsystem\u0026lt;ResourceCache\u0026gt;();\n\n\trenderer-\u0026gt;SetNumViewports(2);\n\n\tFile loadFile(context_,\n\t\t\tGetSubsystem\u0026lt;FileSystem\u0026gt;()-\u0026gt;GetProgramDir()\n\t\t\t+ \"Data/Scenes/MSNMenu.xml\", FILE_READ);\n\tmain_-\u0026gt;scene_-\u0026gt;LoadXML(loadFile);\n\n\tmain_-\u0026gt;cameraNode_ = main_-\u0026gt;scene_-\u0026gt;GetChild(\"camera\");\n\tmain_-\u0026gt;viewport_-\u0026gt;SetCamera(main_-\u0026gt;cameraNode_-\u0026gt;GetComponent\u0026lt;Camera\u0026gt;());\n\n\trenderer-\u0026gt;SetViewport(0, main_-\u0026gt;viewport_);\n\n\tFile loadFile2(context_,\n\t\t\tGetSubsystem\u0026lt;FileSystem\u0026gt;()-\u0026gt;GetProgramDir()\n\t\t\t+ \"Data/Scenes/spaceSimulationMenu.xml\", FILE_READ);\n\tscene_-\u0026gt;LoadXML(loadFile2);\n\n\tcameraNode_ = scene_-\u0026gt;GetChild(\"camera\");\n\n\tSharedPtr\u0026lt;RenderPath\u0026gt; colorUnclearRenderPath = SharedPtr\u0026lt;RenderPath\u0026gt; (new RenderPath());\n\tcolorUnclearRenderPath-\u0026gt;Load(cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;XMLFile\u0026gt;(\"RenderPaths/BackgroundLayer.xml\"));\n\tviewport_ = new Viewport(main_-\u0026gt;GetContext(), scene_, cameraNode_-\u0026gt;GetComponent\u0026lt;Camera\u0026gt;());\n\tviewport_-\u0026gt;SetCamera(cameraNode_-\u0026gt;GetComponent\u0026lt;Camera\u0026gt;());\n\tviewport_-\u0026gt;SetRenderPath(colorUnclearRenderPath);\n\trenderer-\u0026gt;SetViewport(1, viewport_);\n\n\tSubscribeToEvent(E_UPDATE, HANDLER(SpaceSimulationMenuSelect, HandleUpdate));\n}\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;renderpath\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" depth=\"1.0\" stencil=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"base\" vertexlights=\"true\" metadata=\"base\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"forwardlights\" pass=\"light\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postopaque\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"refract\"\u0026gt;\n        \u0026lt;texture unit=\"environment\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"alpha\" vertexlights=\"true\" sort=\"backtofront\" metadata=\"alpha\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postalpha\" sort=\"backtofront\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/renderpath\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:35.818Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":136,"readers_count":135,"score":57.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/how-to-convert-c-to-actionscript/2789","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"How to convert C++ to ActionScript !?","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":140,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":4072,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2015-01-11T19:39:13.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003ethere is my trying to make sceneB( mushrooms + light+ ortho camera) as overlay on sceneA (ground and boxes+ light+ camera).\u003cbr\u003e\nand seems it works correctly\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://savepic.ru/6604446.htm\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://savepic.ru/6604446m.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"\" height=\"\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethe first of all you need copy RenderPath/Forward.xml named it like as RenderPath/ForwardTest.xml  and delete first commad with clear command.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u0026lt;renderpath\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"base\" vertexlights=\"true\" metadata=\"base\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"forwardlights\" pass=\"light\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postopaque\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"refract\"\u0026gt;\n        \u0026lt;texture unit=\"environment\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"alpha\" vertexlights=\"true\" sort=\"backtofront\" metadata=\"alpha\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postalpha\" sort=\"backtofront\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/renderpath\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethen make two scenes, with cameras and some objects.\u003cbr\u003e\nin sceneA you have usual perspective camera, 3d world…\u003cbr\u003e\nin sceneB you must setup camera as ortho and adjust scale, locate some objects before view of camera they will be render as images, add some light\u003cbr\u003e\nsave this two scenes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethis my code for setup example:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e#include \"common.h\"\n#include \"main.h\"\n\nDEFINE_APPLICATION_MAIN(MyApp);\n\nMyApp::MyApp(Context* context) : Application(context)\n{\n\t\tengineParameters_[\"WindowTitle\"] = GetTypeName();\n\t\tengineParameters_[\"FullScreen\"] = false;\n\t\tengineParameters_[\"Headless\"] = false;\n\t\tengineParameters_[\"WindowWidth\"] = 1280;\n\t\tengineParameters_[\"WindowHeight\"] = 720;\n\t\tengineParameters_[\"LogName\"] = GetSubsystem\u0026lt;FileSystem\u0026gt;()-\u0026gt;GetAppPreferencesDir(\"urho3d\", \"logs\") + GetTypeName() + \".log\";\n\t\tengineParameters_[\"RenderPath\"] = \"Bin\\CoreData\\RenderPaths\\Forward.xml\";\n}\n\nvoid MyApp::Setup()\n{\n        // Called before engine initialization. engineParameters_ member variable can be modified here\n}\n\nvoid MyApp::Start()\n{\n\tGraphics* graphics = GetSubsystem\u0026lt;Graphics\u0026gt;();\n\tRenderer* renderer = GetSubsystem\u0026lt;Renderer\u0026gt;();\n\tResourceCache* cache = GetSubsystem\u0026lt;ResourceCache\u0026gt;();\n    // Called after engine initialization. Setup application \u0026amp; subscribe to events here\n    SubscribeToEvent(E_KEYDOWN, HANDLER(MyApp, HandleKeyDown));\n\t\n\tscene1 = SharedPtr\u0026lt;Scene\u0026gt;(new Scene(context_));\n\tFile sceneFile(context_, GetSubsystem\u0026lt;FileSystem\u0026gt;()-\u0026gt;GetProgramDir() + \"Data/Scenes/SceneA.xml\", FILE_READ);\n\tscene1-\u0026gt;LoadXML(sceneFile);\n\t\n\tscene2 = SharedPtr\u0026lt;Scene\u0026gt;(new Scene(context_));\n\tFile sceneFile2(context_, GetSubsystem\u0026lt;FileSystem\u0026gt;()-\u0026gt;GetProgramDir() + \"Data/Scenes/SceneB.xml\", FILE_READ);\n\tscene2-\u0026gt;LoadXML(sceneFile2);\n\n\tcamera1Node = scene1-\u0026gt;GetChild(\"cameraNode\", true);\n\tcamera2Node = scene2-\u0026gt;GetChild(\"cameraNode\", true);\n\n\tcamera1 = camera1Node-\u0026gt;GetComponent\u0026lt;Camera\u0026gt;();\n\tcamera2 = camera2Node-\u0026gt;GetComponent\u0026lt;Camera\u0026gt;();\n\n\tviewport1 = new Viewport(context_, scene1, camera1);\n\tviewport2 = new Viewport(context_, scene2, camera2);\n\n\n\toverlayRenderPath = SharedPtr\u0026lt;RenderPath\u0026gt;(new RenderPath());\n\toverlayRenderPath-\u0026gt;Load(cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;XMLFile\u0026gt;(\"RenderPaths/ForwardTest.xml\"));\n\tviewport2-\u0026gt;SetRenderPath(overlayRenderPath);\n\n\n\trenderer-\u0026gt;SetNumViewports(2);\n\trenderer-\u0026gt;SetViewport(0, viewport1);\n\trenderer-\u0026gt;SetViewport(1, viewport2);\t\n}\n\nvoid MyApp::Stop()\n{\n        // Perform optional cleanup after main loop has terminated\n}\n    \nvoid MyApp::HandleKeyDown(StringHash eventType, VariantMap\u0026amp; eventData)\n{\n        using namespace KeyDown;\n\n        // Check for pressing ESC. Note the engine_ member variable for convenience access to the Engine object\n        int key = eventData[P_KEY].GetInt();\n        if (key == KEY_ESC)\n            engine_-\u0026gt;Exit();\n}\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:35.883Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":24,"reads":113,"readers_count":112,"score":179.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://savepic.ru/6604446.htm","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Просмотр изображения 6604446 - Вставляйте фото и картинки в форумы","clicks":30},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/background-video-texture/2809/3","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Background video texture","clicks":7},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/how-to-stop-weapon-from-clipping-through-objects/3902","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"How to Stop Weapon from Clipping Through Objects","clicks":0},{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/using-texture-as-depth-map-pre-rendered-backgrounds/3461/3","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Using Texture as Depth Map? (Pre-Rendered Backgrounds)","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":148,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":4074,"name":"","username":"practicing01","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/p/b5e925/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-01-11T23:09:47.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks, deleting the entire clear command line worked.  Just incase though, when cadaver  said “If you get trouble with Z-buffering, then you can make the second renderpath clear depth but not color.”, how would I go about doing that?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:36.051Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":98,"readers_count":97,"score":19.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":140,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":4075,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2015-01-12T00:51:43.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003ei guess like that\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\nyou just preserve in clear command only depth \u0026amp; stencil clearning\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:36.109Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":93,"readers_count":92,"score":18.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":148,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":4076,"name":"","username":"practicing01","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/p/b5e925/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-01-12T01:15:28.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIf it’s supposed to be like that then it’s bugged cus it didn’t work.  No worries though, for this project what worked is enough, perhaps in the future I’ll revisit the problem.  Thanks for the help.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:36.172Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":94,"readers_count":93,"score":33.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":140,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":4078,"name":"Lasse Öörni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2015-01-12T09:21:48.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWhen I do  in Forward.xml renderpath I observe the background not getting cleared (ghost effect), so it should work. Not sure if it can fail in a more complex case though. You could examine the clearing RenderPathCommand in code and make sure its clearFlags_ don’t have CLEAR_COLOR bit set.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:02:36.326Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":87,"readers_count":86,"score":17.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"Lasse Öörni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":10636,"name":"","username":"Enhex","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/enhex/{size}/81_2.png","created_at":"2016-03-06T21:57:27.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHow can it be achieved with deferred rendering? Disabling color clear just results in a black background.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt does work with forward.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAlso I noticed that having Bloom effects adds a black tint where it should be transparent.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:10:37.904Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":85,"readers_count":84,"score":27.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":184,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":11076,"name":"","username":"dakilla","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/d/a87d85/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-03-16T13:05:43.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m trying to achieve the same thing, it works using previous example, but how deal blending (add, substract, mul, etc…) or add transparency between viewports ?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethanks\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:11:09.505Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":85,"readers_count":84,"score":22.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":394,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":11082,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2016-03-16T17:27:26.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI suppose in your case you don’t need set second viewport to renderer instead this you probably need add second(overlay RT) to cache.AddManualResource() to allow use it in RenderPath.\u003cbr\u003e\nThen you add quad command with lines like this:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e    \u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" vs=\"YourCustomShaderOrJustCopyBufferShader\" ps=\"YourCustomShaderOrJustCopyBufferShader\" blend=\"add/substract/alpha\" output=\"viewport\"\u0026gt;\n        \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"camera2RT\" /\u0026gt; // same name that put into cache.AddManualResource() \n    \u0026lt;/command\u0026gt; \u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand doing blending overlay scene with main scene. May be you also need create custom shader for quad command to discard pixels by some reason to avoid blending in empty areas of overlay RT or by some another mask RT(or free color channel in already existing RTs).\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:11:09.936Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":80,"readers_count":79,"score":31.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":148,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":11121,"name":"","username":"dakilla","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/d/a87d85/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-03-17T09:11:12.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks, It works as you said.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003eSharedPtr\u0026lt;Texture2D\u0026gt; renderTexture(new Texture2D(context_));\nrenderTexture-\u0026gt;SetSize(graphics-\u0026gt;GetWidth(), graphics-\u0026gt;GetHeight(), Graphics::GetRGBFormat(), TEXTURE_RENDERTARGET);\nrenderTexture-\u0026gt;SetFilterMode(Urho3D::FILTER_DEFAULT);\nrenderTexture-\u0026gt;SetName(\"myrt\");\ncache-\u0026gt;AddManualResource(renderTexture);    \n\nSharedPtr\u0026lt;RenderSurface\u0026gt; surface(renderTexture-\u0026gt;GetRenderSurface());\nSharedPtr\u0026lt;Viewport\u0026gt; rttViewport(new Viewport(context_, scene2, camera2));\nsurface-\u0026gt;SetViewport(0, rttViewport);\nsurface-\u0026gt;SetUpdateMode(SURFACE_UPDATEALWAYS);\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand renderpath :\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" vs=\"CopyFramebufferFlipped\" ps=\"CopyFramebufferFlipped\" blend=\"add\" output=\"viewport\"\u0026gt;\n  \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"myrt\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI used CopyFramebuffer shader but I had to flip uv vertically (opengl).\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:11:12.612Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":18,"reads":82,"readers_count":81,"score":106.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":394,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":11127,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2016-03-17T10:30:15.000Z","cooked":"\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI used CopyFramebuffer shader but I had to flip uv vertically (opengl).\u003cbr\u003e\nYou need flip TexCoords in case using of gl renderer in shader with help something like this:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:11:13.006Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":77,"readers_count":76,"score":20.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":148,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":11128,"name":"","username":"1vanK","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/1vank/{size}/768_2.png","created_at":"2016-03-17T10:52:21.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e[quote=“dakilla”]\u003cbr\u003e\nI used CopyFramebuffer shader but I had to flip uv vertically (opengl).[/quote]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://urho3d.github.io/documentation/HEAD/_a_p_i_differences.html\"\u003eurho3d.github.io/documentation/H … ences.html\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo ensure similar UV addressing for render-to-texture viewports on both APIs, on OpenGL texture viewports will be rendered upside down.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:11:13.068Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":77,"readers_count":76,"score":20.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://urho3d.github.io/documentation/HEAD/_a_p_i_differences.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D - Documentation - Differences between rendering APIs","clicks":12}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":263,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12359,"name":"","username":"dakilla","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/d/a87d85/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-06-04T06:22:36.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI 'm still not comfortable with renderpath, I would like an advice, please.\u003cbr\u003e\nI’m trying to use a custom blending shader for layering scenes (rendered each in rendertargets) but result is not as I expected.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI thought to use the ‘mixed’ rendertarget as blend cascaded result  (output for the 2 first quads) and to use it also as an input in the second quad (in the first quad it will be empty).\u003cbr\u003e\nThe final quad, is for copying final ‘mixed’ to the viewport.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMergingShader just do some math operations using samplers 0 \u0026amp; 1 (texture unit 0 and 1).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut sampler 0 (texture unit=“0” name=\"mixed) always seems to return a black color, why ??\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy renderpath  :\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[code]\u003c/p\u003e\n    \n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"mytag\" vs=\"MergingShader\" ps=\"MergingShader\" blend=\"replace\" output=\"mixed\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"0\" name=\"mixed\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"1\" name=\"rt1\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlendRatio\" value=\"0 0.5\" /\u0026gt;\"\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"ClearColor\" value=\"0 0 0 1\" /\u0026gt;\"\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"MergeMode\" value=\"5\" /\u0026gt;\"\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"FlipUV\" value=\"true\" /\u0026gt;\"\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"mytag\" vs=\"MergingShader\" ps=\"MergingShader\" blend=\"replace\" output=\"mixed\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"0\" name=\"mixed\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"1\" name=\"rt2\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlendRatio\" value=\"0.5 0.5\" /\u0026gt;\"\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"ClearColor\" value=\"0 0 0 1\" /\u0026gt;\"\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"MergeMode\" value=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\"\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"FlipUV\" value=\"true\" /\u0026gt;\"\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt; \n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n   \n        \n    \t\n\u003cp\u003e[/code]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNote : In this example I only have two senes, but in real case it is generated programmaticcally and I can have up to 16 scenes or more (why I blend  cascaded result in mixed instead of using a single quad with multiple texture units)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethanks\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":15,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:41.135Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":78,"readers_count":77,"score":30.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":394,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12360,"name":"Lasse Öörni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2016-06-04T09:16:49.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYou cannot sample and render to an RT at the same time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThere’s a difference of handling the final destination rendertarget “viewport” and named texture rendertargets you have created yourself. The viewport RT will be pingponged automatically by creating an extra texture, since it’s so common and often needed by postprocess effects chains. But for your named RT’s the engine won’t guess how you want this handled. Rather you will have to manage the pingponging (if any is needed) manually by e.g. creating a “mixed2” RT and ensuring you never sample and render the same RT simultaneously.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":16,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:41.210Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":75,"readers_count":74,"score":20.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":740,"topic_slug":"how-to-layer-scenes","display_username":"Lasse Öörni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12361,"name":"","username":"dakilla","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/d/a87d85/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-06-04T11:31:11.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOk I see.\u003cbr\u003e\nIt works using a mixed2 RT and switching alternately.\u003cbr\u003e\nThanks \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=5\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":17,"post_type":1